               Warner Brothers Pictures(2007). Length : 122min                


 The last time we saw Danny Ocean&#039;s crew, they were paying back ruthless      
 casino mogul Terry Benedict after stealing millions from him. However, it&#039;s  
 been a while since they&#039;ve come back together, which is all about to         
 change. When one of their own, Reuben Tishkoff builds a hotel with known     
 casino owner Willy Banks, the last thing he ever wanted was to get cut out   
 of the deal personally by the loathsome Banks. Banks&#039; attitude even goes so  
 far as to finding the amusement in Tishkoff&#039;s misfortune when the double     
 crossing lands Reuben in the hospital because of a heart attack. However,    
 Danny and his crew won&#039;t stand for Banks and what he&#039;s done to a friend.     
 Uniting with their old enemy Benedict, who himself has a vendetta against    
 Banks, the crew is out to pull off a major plan. One that will unfold on     
 the night Banks&#039; newest hot spot opens up, when the crew is out to bankrupt  
 one of the city&#039;s most despised businessmen. But they&#039;re not in this for     
 the money, but for the revenge.
